#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:403
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:403"
msgid "`v0.4.0` - Introduced."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:405
msgid ""
"`ptool.try(fn)` runs `fn` and converts raised errors into return values."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:407
msgid "`fn` (function, required): Callback to execute."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:408
msgid "Returns: `ok, value, err`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:410
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:410"
msgid "Return value rules:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:412
msgid ""
"On success, `ok = true`, `err = nil`, and `value` contains the callback "
"result."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:414
msgid "If the callback returns no values, `value` is `nil`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:415
msgid "If the callback returns one value, `value` is that value."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:416
msgid ""
"If the callback returns multiple values, `value` is an array-like table."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:417
msgid "On failure, `ok = false`, `value = nil`, and `err` is a table."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:419
msgid "Structured error fields:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:421
msgid ""
"`kind` (string): Stable error category such as `io_error`, `command_failed`, "
"`invalid_argument`, `http_error`, or `lua_error`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:423
msgid "`message` (string): Human-readable error message."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:424
msgid "`op` (string, optional): API or operation name such as `ptool.fs.read`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:425
msgid "`detail` (string, optional): Extra detail for the failure."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:426
msgid "`path` (string, optional): Path involved in a filesystem failure."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:427
msgid ""
"`input` (string, optional): Original input that failed to parse or validate."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:428
msgid "`cmd` (string, optional): Command name for command failures."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:429
msgid ""
"`status` (integer, optional): Exit status or HTTP status when available."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:430
msgid "`stderr` (string, optional): Captured stderr for command failures."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:431
msgid "`url` (string, optional): URL involved in an HTTP failure."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:432
msgid ""
"`cwd` (string, optional): Effective working directory for command failures."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:433
msgid ""
"`target` (string, optional): SSH target for SSH-related command failures."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:434
msgid ""
"`retryable` (boolean): Whether retrying may make sense. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:436
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:436"
msgid "Behavior:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:438
msgid ""
"`ptool` APIs raise structured errors. `ptool.try` converts them into the "
"`err` table above so callers can branch on `err.kind` and related fields."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:440
msgid ""
"Plain Lua errors are also caught. In that case, `err.kind` is `lua_error`, "
"and only `message` is guaranteed."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:442
msgid ""
"`ptool.try` is the recommended way to handle errors from APIs such as "
"`ptool.fs.read`, `ptool.http.request`, `ptool.run(..., { check = true })`, "
"`ptool.pipe(..., { check = true })`, and `res:assert_ok()`."
msgstr ""

