msgid "`v0.1.0` - Introduced."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:475
msgid "`ptool.run` executes external commands from Rust."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:477
msgid "The following call forms are supported:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:489
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:489"
msgid "Argument rules:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:491
msgid ""
"`ptool.run(cmdline)`: `cmdline` is split using shell-style (`shlex`) rules. "
"The first item is treated as the command and the rest as arguments."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:493
msgid ""
"`ptool.run(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` is used directly as the command, and "
"`argsline` is split into an argument list using shell-style (`shlex`) rules."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:495
msgid ""
"`ptool.run(cmd, args)`: `cmd` is a string and `args` is an array of strings."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:496
msgid ""
"`ptool.run(cmdline, options)`: `options` overrides settings for this "
"invocation, such as `echo`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:498
msgid ""
"`ptool.run(cmd, args, options)`: `args` can be either a string or an array "
"of strings, and `options` overrides settings for this invocation, such as "
"`echo`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:500
msgid "`ptool.run(options)`: `options` is a table."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:501
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:501"
msgid ""
"When the second argument is a table: if it is an array "
"(consecutive integer keys `1..n`), it is treated as `args`; otherwise it is "
"treated as `options`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:504
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:504"
msgid "Return value rules:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid "A table is always returned with the following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid "`ok` (boolean): Whether the exit code is `0`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid ""
"`code` (integer|nil): The process exit code. If the process was terminated "
"by a signal, this is `nil`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid "`cmd` (string): Command name used for the execution."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid "`cwd` (string): Effective working directory used for the execution."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid "`stdout` (string, optional): Present when `stdout = \"capture\"`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid "`stderr` (string, optional): Present when `stderr = \"capture\"`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:506
msgid ""
"`assert_ok(self)` (function): Raises a structured error when `ok = false`. "
"The error kind is `command_failed`, and the error may include `cmd`, `status`"
", `stderr`, and `cwd`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:517
msgid ""
"The default value of `check` comes from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { check = ... } })`. If not configured, it defaults to `false`. "
"When `check = false`, callers can inspect `ok` themselves or call "
"`res:assert_ok()`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:520
msgid ""
"When both `check = true` and `retry = true`, `ptool.run` asks whether the "
"failed command should be retried before raising the final error."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:522
msgid ""
"When `check = true`, `ptool.run` raises the same structured `command_failed` "
"error that `res:assert_ok()` raises. Use `ptool.try(...)` if you want to "
"catch and inspect it from Lua."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:526
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:526"
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:547
msgid ""
"`ptool.run(options)` is also supported, where `options` is a table with the "
"following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:550
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:550"
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:551
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:551"
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:552
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:552"
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): The child process working directory."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:553
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:553"
msgid ""
"`env` (table, optional): Additional environment variables, where keys are "
"variable names and values are variable values."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:555
msgid ""
"`sudo` (boolean, optional): Whether to run the command through `sudo` when "
"the current user is not root. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:557
msgid "`stdin` (string|table, optional): Child process stdin source."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:557
msgid "A string sends that string to the child process stdin."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:557
msgid "A table `{ file = \"path\" }` reads stdin from a file."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:557
msgid "When omitted, the child process inherits the current process stdin."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:561
msgid ""
"`trim` (boolean, optional): Whether to trim leading and trailing whitespace "
"from captured `stdout` and captured `stderr` before returning them. This "
"only affects streams set to `\"capture\"`. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:564
msgid ""
"`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo command information for this "
"execution. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config({ run = { echo = ... } })"
"` is used; if that is also unset, the default is `true`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:567
msgid ""
"`check` (boolean, optional): Whether to raise an error immediately when the "
"exit code is not `0`. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { check = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is "
"`false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:570
msgid ""
"`confirm` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user for confirmation "
"before execution. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { confirm = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default "
"is `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:573
msgid ""
"`retry` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user whether to retry after "
"a failed execution when `check = true`. If omitted, the value from "
"`ptool.config({ run = { retry = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, "
"the default is `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577"
msgid "`stdout` (string|table, optional): Stdout handling strategy."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577"
msgid "`\"inherit\"`: Inherit to the current terminal (default)."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577
msgid "`\"capture\"`: Capture into `res.stdout`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577"
msgid "`\"null\"`: Discard the output."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577"
msgid "`{ file = \"path\" }`: Write stdout to a file, truncating it first."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:577"
msgid "`{ file = \"path\", append = true }`: Append stdout to a file."
