msgid ""
"`options` supports the same per-call fields as `ptool.run(options)` except "
"that `cmd` and `args` are replaced by the positional `stages` table."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:733
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:733"
msgid ""
"The default `echo`, `check`, `confirm`, and `retry` values still come from "
"`ptool.config({ run = { ... } })`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:735
msgid "`stdin` is connected to the first stage."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:736
msgid "`stdout` refers to the last stage output."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:737
msgid "`stderr` applies to all stages."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:738
msgid ""
"When `check = true`, any failed stage raises a structured `command_failed` "
"error, and `retry = true` prompts to rerun the whole pipeline."
