msgid "ptool.run_capture"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:763
msgid "`v0.6.0` - Introduced."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:765
msgid ""
"`ptool.run_capture` executes external commands from Rust with the same call "
"forms, argument rules, return value rules, and options as `ptool.run`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:768
msgid "The difference is only the default stream handling:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:770
msgid "`stdout` defaults to `\"capture\"`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:771
msgid "`stderr` defaults to `\"capture\"`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:773
msgid ""
"`trim` still defaults to `false`, and you can still override any of these "
"fields explicitly in `options`."
