#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:802
msgid "ptool.exec"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:804
msgid "`v0.7.0` - Introduced."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:806
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec` replaces the current `ptool` process with an external command."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:808
msgid "It supports the same command argument call forms as `ptool.run`:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:819
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:819"
msgid "Behavior:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:821
msgid ""
"On success, `ptool.exec` does not return. The current `ptool` process is "
"replaced by the target command."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:823
msgid "Any Lua code after a successful `ptool.exec(...)` call does not run."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:824
msgid ""
"In `ptool repl`, a successful `ptool.exec(...)` also replaces the REPL "
"process."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:826
msgid "On Unix platforms, this uses true process replacement semantics."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:827
msgid ""
"On non-Unix platforms, `ptool.exec` currently raises an `unsupported` error."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:829
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:829"
msgid "Argument rules:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:831
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec(cmdline)`: `cmdline` is split using shell-style (`shlex`) rules. "
"The first item is treated as the command and the rest as arguments."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:833
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` is used directly as the command, and "
"`argsline` is split into an argument list using shell-style (`shlex`) rules."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:835
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec(cmd, args)`: `cmd` is a string and `args` is an array of strings."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:836
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec(cmdline, options)`: `options` overrides settings for this "
"invocation, such as `echo`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:838
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec(cmd, args, options)`: `args` can be either a string or an array "
"of strings, and `options` overrides settings for this invocation, such as "
"`confirm`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:841
msgid "`ptool.exec(options)`: `options` is a table."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:842
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:842"
msgid ""
"When the second argument is a table: if it is an array "
"(consecutive integer keys `1..n`), it is treated as `args`; otherwise it is "
"treated as `options`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:845
msgid ""
"`ptool.exec(options)` is also supported, where `options` is a table with the "
"following fields:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:848
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:848"
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:849
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:849"
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:850
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:850"
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): The child process working directory."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:851
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:851"
msgid ""
"`env` (table, optional): Additional environment variables, where keys are "
"variable names and values are variable values."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:853
msgid ""
"`sudo` (boolean, optional): Whether to run the replacement command through "
"`sudo` when the current user is not root. Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:855
msgid "`stdin` (table, optional): Child process stdin source."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:855
msgid "`{ file = \"path\" }`: Read stdin from a file."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:857
msgid ""
"`echo` (boolean, optional): Whether to echo command information before "
"replacement. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { echo = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default is "
"`true`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:860
msgid ""
"`confirm` (boolean, optional): Whether to ask the user for confirmation "
"before replacement. If omitted, the value from `ptool.config"
"({ run = { confirm = ... } })` is used; if that is also unset, the default "
"is `false`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863"
msgid "`stdout` (string|table, optional): Stdout handling strategy."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863"
msgid "`\"inherit\"`: Inherit to the current terminal (default)."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863"
msgid "`\"null\"`: Discard the output."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863"
msgid "`{ file = \"path\" }`: Write stdout to a file, truncating it first."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:863"
msgid "`{ file = \"path\", append = true }`: Append stdout to a file."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868"
msgid "`stderr` (string|table, optional): Stderr handling strategy."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868"
msgid "`\"inherit\"`: Inherit to the current terminal (default)."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868"
msgid "`\"null\"`: Discard the output."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868"
msgid "`{ file = \"path\" }`: Write stderr to a file, truncating it first."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:868"
msgid "`{ file = \"path\", append = true }`: Append stderr to a file."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:873
msgid ""
"Unlike `ptool.run`, `ptool.exec` does not support string `stdin`, `stdout = "
"\"capture\"`, `stderr = \"capture\"`, `trim`, `check`, or `retry`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:875
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:875"
msgid ""
"File redirect paths are resolved relative to the effective child-process "
"`cwd`, unless an absolute path is provided."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:877
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:877"
msgid "When `sudo = true`:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:877
msgid ""
"If the current user is already root, `ptool.exec(...)` replaces the current "
"process with the command directly."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:877
msgid ""
"Otherwise, `ptool.exec(...)` replaces the current process with `sudo <cmd> "
"<args...>`."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:877
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:877"
msgid "On Windows, this currently raises an `unsupported` error."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:883
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:883"
msgid "When `confirm = true`:"
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:883
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:883"
msgid "If the user refuses the execution, an error is raised immediately."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:883
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:883"
msgid ""
"If the current environment is not interactive (no TTY), an error is raised "
"immediately."
msgstr ""

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:888
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/core.md:888"
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""
